President Obama expresses his condolences to the medical professionals and civilians affected by the tragic incident at a Doctors Without Borders hospital in Kunduz. The Department of Defense is conducting a full investigation, and the President will await the results before making a definitive judgment. He has asked to be kept informed of the investigation and expects a thorough accounting of the facts and circumstances. The President and First Lady offer their thoughts and prayers to all those affected by the incident. The United States will continue to work with President Ghani, the Afghan government, and international partners to support the Afghan National Defense and Security forces in securing their country.